Vice President Mike Pence delivers a speech in Estonia, expressing the United States' support for the Baltic States and their fight for independence. He emphasizes the strong bond between the US and the Baltic States, praising their commitment to NATO and their contributions to international security. Pence also condemns Russia's attempts to redraw international borders through force and emphasizes the US's commitment to mutual defense through Article 5. He discusses the importance of security for prosperity and the potential for expanding economic ties between the US and the Baltic States. Pence concludes by expressing confidence in the future of the US-Baltic relationship.